    "body": "Problem:\r\n\r\nStandalone `nvim -ll` scripts do not provide `vim.wait()`, so tests and\r\nhelper scripts that rely on luv timers need to open-code their own\r\npolling loops.\r\n\r\nSolution:\r\n\r\nLoad a luv-backed `vim.wait()` implementation in standalone mode,\r\ndocument the `-ll` semantics, and add functional coverage for\r\ntimer-driven success and timeout behavior.\r\n\r\nAI-assisted: Codex\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nRelated #38116 ",
    "closed_at": null,
    "comment_data": [],
    "comment_regular_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "`nvim -ll` is temporary, and ideally we could drop it in favor of `nvim -l`.\r\n\r\nMeanwhile, is it not possible to make the existing `vim.wait` available for `-ll` ? \r\n\r\nThough with https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/38116 if we can eliminate the C impl of `vim.wait`, that's another alternative",
