        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> Oh. I thought `-ll` was a very useful feature, basically a drop-in replacement for `lua`\r\n\r\nwell if we're adding features like this then that indicates that `nvim -l` features are wanted :)\r\n\r\nbut maybe i'm not aware of why it's important for us to have a \"pure\" lua mode.\r\n \r\n> That was my thinking. Should we merge #38116 first?\r\n\r\nthat would be my preference, rather than having both things temporarily. though i would like to find time to review #38116 ",
            "created_at": "2026-04-16T11:39:12Z",
